<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-03"><hi rend="italic">January 3,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Instructions in telegram of 2d anticipated and executed. Nine hundred
                            just killed between Ourfa and Aintab. Road is not safe for Miss
                            Shattuck, who wires she is well, but distressed. Porte declares
                            missionary <pb facs="0710" n="1444" xml:id="pg_1444"/> statement that
                            soldiers pillaged boarding school at Marash to be calumny, and says
                            missionaries sent address of thanks for protection there afforded. It
                            may have been sent, for the poor men were in fearful duress.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>